'''Pau Cubarsí Paredes''' (born 22 January 2007) is a Spanish professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[centre-back]] for {{Spanish football updater|Barcelona}} club [[FC Barcelona|Barcelona]] and the [[Spain national football team|Spain national team]]. In July 2025, [[Sports Illustrated]] and [[ESPN]] ranked Cubarsí as the sixth-best centre-back in world football.<ref>{{cite web |date=9 July 2025 |title=The 25 Best Centre Backs in World Soccer—Ranked |url=https://www.si.com/soccer/the-best-centre-backs-in-world-soccer-ranked |access-date=10 August 2025 |website=Sports Illustrated}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |date=4 June 2025 |title=2025 FC 100: Van Dijk among best center backs in men's soccer |url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/story/_/id/45165487/2025-fc-100-virgil-van-dijk-best-center-backs-mens-soccer |access-date=10 August 2025 |website=ESPN}}</ref>

== Early and personal life ==
Pau Cubarsí Paredes was born on 22 January 2007 in [[Bescanó]], [[Province of Girona|Girona]], [[Catalonia]],<ref name="md" /> to Gloria Paredes and Robert Cubarsí. He has an older sister, Irene, a physiotherapist.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Chauhan |first=Saransh |date=26 October 2024 |title=Introducing Pau Cubarsi's Family- All About Barcelona Star's Parents, Girlfriend, Sister & More |url=https://www.essentiallysports.com/soccer-football-news-introducing-pau-cubarsi-family-all-about-barcelona-stars-parents-girlfriend-sister-more/ |access-date=4 July 2025 |website=EssentiallySports |language=en}}</ref> He joined La Masia in 2018, located about an hour and a half away from his home in Bescanó.<ref>{{Cite news |last=Herrero |first=Laia Cervelló |date=9 May 2024 |title=Pau Cubarsi's Barcelona story and the tiny Catalan village that shaped him |url=https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/5726282/2024/09/05/pau-cubarsi-barcelona-la-liga-la-masia/ |access-date=4 July 2025 |work=The New York Times |language=en-US |issn=0362-4331}}</ref>

Cubarsí speaks [[Catalan language|Catalan]], the language he grew up with, as his parents spoke it as the main language at home. While playing for Spain at the Olympic Games in 2024, he said that he rarely took part in interviews because he was not fluent speaking [[Spanish language|Spanish]], having only ever lived in Catalonia and used his native language.<ref>{{Cite web |date=26 July 2024 |title=Pau Cubarsí reconoce tener problemas para hablar en castellano: "He hablado toda la vida en catalán" |url=https://www.lavanguardia.com/cribeo/viral/20240726/9830973/pau-cubarsi-reconoce-problemas-hablar-castellano-hablado-vida-catalan-mmn.html |access-date=27 July 2024 |website=La Vanguardia |language=es}}</ref>

==Club career==
Cubarsí began his career with [[Girona FC|Girona]], before the move to [[FC Barcelona|Barcelona]] in 2018.<ref name=md>{{cite news |url=https://www.mundodeportivo.com/futbol/fc-barcelona/20221101/1001889656/pau-cubarsi-15-anos-tercer-debutante-mas-joven-barca-uefa-yout-league.html |title=Pau Cubarsí, 15 años, tercer debutante más joven del Barça en la UEFA Youth League |trans-title=Pau Cubarsí, 15 years old, Barça's third youngest debutant in the UEFA Youth League |first=Javier |last=Gascón |date=1 November 2022 |access-date=25 August 2023 |work=Mundo Deportivo |language=es}}</ref> Having progressed through the academy, he became the third-youngest Barcelona player to debut in the [[UEFA Youth League]], behind [[Lamine Yamal]] and [[Ilaix Moriba]], when he started in an eventual 1–1 draw with Czech side [[FC Viktoria Plzeň|Viktoria Plzeň]].<ref name=md/>

In April 2023, he trained with the first team for the first time, having been called up by manager [[Xavi (footballer, born 1980)|Xavi]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.sport.es/es/noticias/barca/pau-cubarsi-quien-es-86251194 |title=¿Quién es Pau Cubarsí? |trans-title=Who is Pau Cubarsí? |date=20 April 2023 |access-date=25 August 2023 |website=sport.es |language=es}}</ref> He signed his first professional contract with the club three months later, on 8 July.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.sport.es/es/noticias/barca/pau-cubarsi-firma-continuidad-barcelona-juvenil-89646238 |title=Pau Cubarsí firma su continuidad en el Juvenil del FC Barcelona |trans-title=Pau Cubarsí signs his continuity in the Juvenil of FC Barcelona |date=8 July 2023 |access-date=25 August 2023 |website=sport.es |language=es}}</ref> He was included in Barcelona's pre-season squad ahead of the 2023–24 season.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.lavanguardia.com/deportes/fc-barcelona/20230710/9100517/asi-transcurrio-primer-entrenamiento-barca-xavi-23-24.html |title=Así transcurrió el primer entrenamiento del Barça de Xavi 23-24 |trans-title=This is how Xavi's first Barça training session went 23-24 |first=Anaïs |last=Martí |date=10 July 2023 |access-date=25 August 2023 |work=La Vanguardia |language=es}}</ref>

On 18 January 2024, Cubarsí made his first team debut against [[Unionistas de Salamanca CF|Unionistas de Salamanca]] in the [[2023–24 Copa del Rey|Copa del Rey]], being subbed on in the 46th minute.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.fcbarcelona.com/en/news/3861192/unionistas-de-salamanca-1-3-fc-barcelona-one-step-closer |title=Unionistas de Salamanca 1–3 FC Barcelona: One step closer |publisher=FC Barcelona |date=18 January 2024}}</ref> His first start came in the next match against [[Real Betis]] in La Liga, a day before his 17th birthday.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.fcbarcelona.com/en/news/3864060/record-breaking-xi-against-betis |title=Record breaking XI against Betis |publisher=FC Barcelona |date=21 January 2024}}</ref> Two months later, on 12 March, he was named Player of the Match on his [[UEFA Champions League]] debut in a 3–1 victory over [[SSC Napoli|Napoli]] in the [[2023–24 UEFA Champions League knockout phase|round of 16]] second leg, in which he became the youngest player to debut at 17 years and 50 days in the competition's knockout phase, breaking former [[FC Bayern Munich|Bayern Munich]] defender [[David Alaba]]'s previous record of 17 years and 258 days.<ref name=":0">{{Cite web |url=https://www.goal.com/en/lists/barcelona-pau-cubarsi-club-champions-league-record-20-years-man-of-the-match-napoli/blt70b32f8b2a8d7384#cs19ae1dd447457ea2 |title=Barcelona teenage sensation Pau Cubarsi breaks club Champions League record in place for 20 years with man-of-the-match display in European debut against Napoli |publisher=[[Goal (website)|Goal]] |date=13 March 2024}}</ref><ref name=":2">{{Cite web |title=FC Barcelona made a New Monster out of Pau Cubarsi |url=https://www.soccersat.com/news/FC-Barcelona-made-New-Monster-out-of-PAU-CUBARSI |website=Soccersat |access-date=26 March 2024}}</ref> On 10 April, Cubarsí has become the youngest defender to start in the quarter finals of the Champions League aged only 17 years and 79 days breaking the previous record held by [[PFC CSKA Moscow|CSKA Moscow]]'s [[Georgi Shchennikov]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.fcbarcelona.com/en/news/3959898/pau-cubarsi-a-record-breaking-centre-half/amp |title=Pau Cubarsí, a record breaking centre half |publisher=FC Barcelona |date=10 April 2024}}</ref> On 9 May, [[FC Barcelona|Barcelona]] announced that they had reached an agreement with Cubarsí for an extension until 30 June 2029, which has a 500 million euro buyout clause.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Agreement to extend Pau Cubarsí contract to 2027 |url=https://www.fcbarcelona.com/en/football/first-team/news/4001116/agreement-to-extend-pau-cubarsi-contract-to-2027/featured |website=FC Barcelona |date=9 May 2024}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |first1=Colin |last1=Millar |first2=Pol |last2=Ballús |title=Barcelona's Cubarsi signs contract extension through to 2027 |url=https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/5481844/2024/05/09/pau-cubarsi-barcelona-contract-new/ |website=[[The Athletic]] |access-date=9 May 2024}}</ref>

On 25 February 2025, Cubarsí headed in his first goal for Barcelona, in a [[2024–25 Copa del Rey|Copa Del Rey]] semi-final against [[Atlético Madrid]] which ended in a 4–4 draw.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.fcbarcelona.com/en/football/first-team/news/4223961/pau-cubarsi-scores-first-blaugrana-goal |title=Pau Cubarsí scores first blaugrana goal |publisher=FC Barcelona |date=25 February 2025}}</ref>

Cubarsí started in Barcelona's 5–0 win over Athletic Club in the 2026 Spanish Super Cup semi‑final, earning praise for a composed display in defence on a big stage.<ref>{{Cite web |last=read |first=Gill Clark·1 min |date=8 January 2026 |title='Everyone wants a Clasico' – Pau Cubarsi hoping to face Real Madrid in Spanish Super Cup final |url=https://sports.yahoo.com/articles/everyone-wants-clasico-pau-cubarsi-120000336.html |access-date=11 January 2026 |website=Yahoo Sports |language=en-US}}</ref>

==International career==
[[File:Uzbekistan vs. Spain, 2024 Summer Olympic men's association football, 2024-07-24 (250) - Pau Cubarsí.jpg|thumb|150px|Cubarsí playing for [[Spain national under-23 football team|Spain U23]] in the [[Football at the 2024 Summer Olympics – Men's tournament|2024 Summer Olympics]]]]

Cubarsí has represented Spain from under-15 to senior level.<ref name=wf>{{WorldFootball.net|pau-cubarsi}}</ref> In March 2024, he was called up to the senior [[Spain national football team|Spain]] team for the first time by coach [[Luis de la Fuente (footballer, born 1961)|Luis de la Fuente]], debuting in a 1–0 friendly loss to [[Colombia national football team|Colombia]].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.marca.com/futbol/barcelona/2024/03/15/65f4291822601dc23a8b45c9.html |title=Pau Cubarsí vive en una nube: 17 años, puede hacer historia en la selección, titular con el Barça, MVP en Champions... |newspaper=[[Marca (newspaper)|Marca]] |date=15 March 2024 |language=es}}</ref> He came on as a substitute in the 83rd minute replacing [[Aymeric Laporte]], in which he became the youngest defender to ever play for Spain at the age of 17 years one month and 28 days, breaking the record previously held by [[Sergio Ramos]] in 2005.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.goal.com/en/lists/barcelona-pau-cubarsi-reacts-spain-youngest-ever-defender-defeat-colombia/bltbd9cc91411fbc73e#csd72043ee7faecd23 |title=Barcelona starlet Pau Cubarsi reacts to becoming Spain's youngest-ever defender in defeat to Colombia |website=[[Goal (website)|Goal]] |date=23 March 2024}}</ref>

On 27 May 2024, Cubarsí was named in the 29-man preliminary squad for the [[UEFA Euro 2024]].<ref>{{cite news |date=27 May 2024 |title=Euro 2024 provisional squad |url=https://rfef.es/en/noticias/euro-2024-provisional-squad |publisher=[[Royal Spanish Football Federation]] |access-date=30 May 2024}}</ref> However, on 7 June, he was excluded from the final squad prior to the tournament.<ref>{{cite news |date=7 June 2024 |title=Official {{!}} Final Spain squad for the Euro 2024 finals |url=https://rfef.es/en/noticias/final-spain-squad-for-the-euro-2024-finals |publisher=[[Royal Spanish Football Federation]] |access-date=7 June 2024 }}</ref>

In July 2024, Cubarsí was selected in the [[Spain national under-23 football team|Spain under-23]] squad for the [[2024 Summer Olympics]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/5592546/2024/06/26/spain-soccer-olympics-squad/|title=Spain name men’s football squad for Paris Olympics: Barcelona’s Pau Cubarsi, Fermin Lopez included|website=The Athletic|publisher=The New York Times|date=26 June 2024}}</ref> He and Spain would go on to win the Olympic [[Football at the 2024 Summer Olympics – Men's tournament final|gold medal]] at the men's football event in the Olympics.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.fcbarcelona.com/en/news/4079356/fermin-eric-and-cubarsi-win-gold|title=Fermín, Eric and Cubarsí win gold
|website=FC Barcelona|date=9 August 2024}}</ref> On 25 May 2026, he was included in Spain's 26-man squad for the [[2026 FIFA World Cup]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://rfef.es/es/noticias/los-26-que-buscaran-volver-reinar-en-el-mundial |title=Los 26 que buscarán volver a reinar en el Mundial |trans-title=The 26 who will seek to reign again in the World Cup |publisher=[[Royal Spanish Football Federation]] |date=25 May 2026 |access-date=25 May 2026 |language=es |url-status=live |archive-date=25 May 2026 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20260525152452/https://rfef.es/es/noticias/los-26-que-buscaran-volver-reinar-en-el-mundial}}</ref>

